{"id":94,"parent_id":74,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":94,"title":"John 20: Believing in the Resurrection of Jesus Christ","subtitle":"","short_title":"John 20: Believing in the Resurrection of Jesus Christ","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ"},[".heading",{"id":"head21","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.head21"},["h1","John 20"],[".subtitle","Believing in the Resurrection of Jesus Christ"],[".intro","The Savior’s mortal ministry ended on the cross, but the empty tomb testified of His divinity and gave hope of a resurrection for all of us. What evidence is there that Jesus Christ was resurrected? Why do you not need to see Him to believe that He has risen from the dead? Ponder John’s testimony in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.31"},"John 20:31"],"before you read and study this chapter."]],[".bodyBlock",[".",{"id":"f90","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.f90"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-092-1.gif"}]],[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20"},"John 20"]],["p.para",{"id":"p388","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.p388"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.1-2"},"John 20:1–2"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/28.1-8"},"Matthew 28:1–8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/16.1-8"},"Mark 16:1–8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/24.1-9"},"Luke 24:1–9"]],["p.para",{"id":"p389","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.p389"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.3-10"},"John 20:3–10"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/24.12"},"Luke 24:12"]],["p.para",{"id":"p390","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.p390"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.19-23"},"John 20:19–23"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/16.14"},"Mark 16:14"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/24.36-48"},"Luke 24:36–48"]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f91","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.f91"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20"},"John 20"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Napkin"],"(v. 7)"],["td","Cloth covering the face of a dead person"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","First day of the week"],"(vv. 1, 19)"],["td","Sunday"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Remit, remitted"],"(v. 23)"],["td","Forgive, forgiven"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.17"},"John 20:17"],"—Where Was the Lord’s Spirit While His Body Lay in the Tomb?"],["p.para",{"id":"p394","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.p394"},"When the resurrected Savior appeared to Mary Magdalene, He said, “I am not yet ascended to my Father.” Where had His spirit gone then while His body lay in the tomb? Peter taught that “he went and preached unto the spirits in prison” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-pet/3.18-20"},"1 Peter 3:18–20"],"). On 3 October 1918, President Joseph F. Smith was pondering that account by Peter. He received in vision a more extensive view of the Savior’s three-day mission (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138"},"D&C 138"],")."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p395","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.p395"},"Do activity A as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20"},"John 20"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Christ the Lord Is Risen"],["p.para",{"id":"p396","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.p396"},"How can we know that Jesus Christ was resurrected?",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20"},"John 20"],"records three levels of knowledge concerning the Resurrection. Discover these levels by reading the references below and answering the accompanying questions:"],[".figure",{"id":"f92","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.f92"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.1-10"},"John 20:1–10"],". What evidence do these verses give of the Resurrection? How is an empty tomb evidence? How did the empty tomb affect what Mary Magdalene, Peter, and “that other disciple” (John) believed?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","What new evidence was given to Mary Magdalene? (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.11-18"},"vv. 11–18"],"). How did this experience affect Mary’s belief regarding the Resurrection of the Savior?"]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","According to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/20.19-20"},"John 20:19–20"],", after the Lord had appeared to ten of the Apostles, what did Thomas require before he would believe their story of seeing the Lord? What new evidence did Thomas receive about the Resurrection? What important principle did the Lord teach Thomas about believing in the Resurrection?"]]]],["p.para",{"id":"p400","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.p400"},"How can you know that Jesus was resurrected? Write your testimony of the Resurrection of Jesus Christ."]]]],[".resources",[".",{"id":"f93","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-john/john-20-believing-in-the-resurrection-of-jesus-christ.f93"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-092-2.gif"}]]]]]],"refs":null}
